down by the court system.

00:38:35.730 --> 00:38:39.545 align:middle line:84%
They had really great
evidence obviously.

00:38:39.545 --> 00:38:41.670 align:middle line:84%
And if you had forced these
companies, these banks,

00:38:41.670 --> 00:38:44.910 align:middle line:84%
to pay the fines for
each one of these sheets

00:38:44.910 --> 00:38:48.960 align:middle line:84%
that they had forged,
they would go bankrupt.

00:38:48.960 --> 00:38:50.917 align:middle line:84%
That's how many
there are, and that's

00:38:50.917 --> 00:38:52.000 align:middle line:90%
how big the penalties are.

00:38:52.000 --> 00:38:55.760 align:middle line:84%
If you had a government that was
interested in true enforcement,

00:38:55.760 --> 00:38:58.840 align:middle line:84%
that could be used as leverage
to break up the banks.

00:38:58.840 --> 00:39:00.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But they're
not going to do that.

00:39:00.910 --> 00:39:05.370 align:middle line:84%
And so the average person
just becomes docile and says,

00:39:05.370 --> 00:39:07.200 align:middle line:84%
well, I can't do
anything about it.

00:39:07.200 --> 00:39:08.820 align:middle line:84%
>>ZEUS: Right, because
they don't have the money

00:39:08.820 --> 00:39:10.111 align:middle line:90%
to go through the court system.

00:39:10.111 --> 00:39:11.860 align:middle line:84%
And even if they
do, they have judges

00:39:11.860 --> 00:39:15.090 align:middle line:84%
that are siding with these
banks, against the law,

00:39:15.090 --> 00:39:16.760 align:middle line:90%
against precedent.

00:39:16.760 --> 00:39:20.160 align:middle line:90%
And they're like, what can I do?

00:39:20.160 --> 00:39:21.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That is true.

00:39:21.320 --> 00:39:24.780 align:middle line:84%
>>ZEUS: And there's the
practical life aspect, too.

00:39:24.780 --> 00:39:26.800 align:middle line:84%
Are you going to
consume your life

00:39:26.800 --> 00:39:31.320 align:middle line:84%
in being consumed in this
litigation when you're already

00:39:31.320 --> 00:39:32.737 align:middle line:84%
behind the eight
ball financially?

00:39:32.737 --> 00:39:34.278 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But some
people just choose

00:39:34.278 --> 00:39:37.000 align:middle line:84%
to stay until the sheriff's
department comes and gives them

00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:39.196 align:middle line:84%
a 3-day or a 30-day
or whatever notice.

00:39:39.196 --> 00:39:40.570 align:middle line:84%
And some people
have been staying

00:39:40.570 --> 00:39:41.830 align:middle line:90%
in those homes for years.

00:39:41.830 --> 00:39:43.660 align:middle line:84%
>>ZEUS: Yes, yes,
for several years.

00:39:43.660 --> 00:39:45.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now what is
your feeling on that?

00:39:45.870 --> 00:39:49.360 align:middle line:84%
And if someone were in
that situation, what would

00:39:49.360 --> 00:39:51.680 align:middle line:90%
you say to them?

00:39:51.680 --> 00:39:54.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ZEUS: Well, I
mean, I don't know.

00:39:54.400 --> 00:39:56.520 align:middle line:84%
Certainly a person
who responsibly

00:39:56.520 --> 00:39:59.230 align:middle line:84%
pays their mortgage
would say, listen.

00:39:59.230 --> 00:40:00.030 align:middle line:90%
Wait a minute.

00:40:00.030 --> 00:40:01.360 align:middle line:84%
You're living in
your house for free

00:40:01.360 --> 00:40:03.970 align:middle line:84%
after you've been irresponsible,
and I'm paying for my house

00:40:03.970 --> 00:40:05.430 align:middle line:90%
while I've been responsible?

00:40:05.430 --> 00:40:08.210 align:middle line:84%
So in general, I'd
say, I don't like that.

00:40:08.210 --> 00:40:10.340 align:middle line:84%
But here's where
two wrongs almost

00:40:10.340 --> 00:40:12.310 align:middle line:84%
do make a right, to
a certain extent.

00:40:12.310 --> 00:40:14.275 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, I totally
get what you're saying,

00:40:14.275 --> 00:40:15.150 align:middle line:90%
and I agree with you.

00:40:15.150 --> 00:40:16.983 align:middle line:84%
>>ZEUS: Because what
happens is that a house

00:40:16.983 --> 00:40:18.620 align:middle line:90%
falls into disrepair, right?

00:40:18.620 --> 00:40:20.350 align:middle line:84%
The bank's not going
to sell it anyway

00:40:20.350 --> 00:40:21.680 align:middle line:84%
because they don't want
to take the loss on it.

00:40:21.680 --> 00:40:22.990 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now the
lawn's overgrown.

00:40:22.990 --> 00:40:23.870 align:middle line:84%
>>ZEUS: Now the
lawn's overgrown.

00:40:23.870 --> 00:40:25.370 align:middle line:84%
The neighborhood
is being overgrown.

00:40:25.370 --> 00:40:27.274 align:middle line:84%
At least they're
mowing the lawn.

00:40:27.274 --> 00:40:28.690 align:middle line:84%
At least they're
paying the taxes,

00:40:28.690 --> 00:40:30.720 align:middle line:84%
and they're paying the
utilities on the house.

00:40:30.720 --> 00:40:34.690 align:middle line:84%
So it's like, you know,
doing the immoral thing

00:40:34.690 --> 00:40:37.396 align:middle line:84%
is still making the better
out of a really bad situation.

00:40:37.396 --> 00:40:39.860 align:middle line:90%


00:40:39.860 --> 00:40:41.805 align:middle line:84%
The complication,
though, doesn't come out

00:40:41.805 --> 00:40:43.180 align:middle line:84%
of these simplistic
moral things.

00:40:43.180 --> 00:40:43.970 align:middle line:90%
Someone's responsible.

00:40:43.970 --> 00:40:44.380 align:middle line:90%
They're paying.

00:40:44.380 --> 00:40:46.046 align:middle line:84%
Someone's irresponsible,
and they don't.

00:40:46.046 --> 00:40:48.470 align:middle line:84%
And I would encourage
the listeners or viewers

00:40:48.470 --> 00:40:52.330 align:middle line:84%
here not to allow yourself
to be pulled back into that.

00:40:52.330 --> 00:40:55.900 align:middle line:84%
Who were the real crooks
here who set this thing up?

00:40:55.900 --> 00:40:57.330 align:middle line:84%
Is it the
irresponsible borrowers

00:40:57.330 --> 00:40:59.079 align:middle line:84%
who should have known
what they were doing

00:40:59.079 --> 00:41:00.410 align:middle line:90%
and failed to pay it off?

00:41:00.410 --> 00:41:02.200 align:middle line:84%
Or is it these people
like these mortgage

00:41:02.200 --> 00:41:05.920 align:middle line:84%
lenders who were forging,
who were signing and getting

00:41:05.920 --> 00:41:06.720 align:middle line:90%
people.

00:41:06.720 --> 00:41:08.370 align:middle line:90%
I'll get you into that house.

00:41:08.370 --> 00:41:09.720 align:middle line:90%
And then it goes.

00:41:09.720 --> 00:41:11.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now we're going
to go away from those 10

00:41:11.970 --> 00:41:16.510 align:middle line:84%
toxic steps as to how we got
here to the 5 courageous steps

00:41:16.510 --> 00:41:18.350 align:middle line:90%
to transform the economy.

00:41:18.350 --> 00:41:20.670 align:middle line:84%
And you start with number
one, which is pierce

00:41:20.670 --> 00:41:23.210 align:middle line:90%
the fantasy or nail the issue.

00:41:23.210 --> 00:41:25.400 align:middle line:90%
Now what do you mean by that?

00:41:25.400 --> 00:41:27.820 align:middle line:84%
>>ZEUS: Well, I
think we had talked

00:41:27.820 --> 00:41:32.390 align:middle line:84%
about the American dream, and
the American dream and sort

00:41:32.390 --> 00:41:33.560 align:middle line:90%
of the false American dream.

00:41:33.560 --> 00:41:37.760 align:middle line:84%
The false American
dream is, I can consume

00:41:37.760 --> 00:41:41.290 align:middle line:90%
my way into the good life.

00:41:41.290 --> 00:41:43.740 align:middle line:84%
If I just play the
game, you know,

00:41:43.740 --> 00:41:45.240 align:middle line:90%
I can get a higher paying job.

00:41:45.240 --> 00:41:46.420 align:middle line:90%
I can buy more things.

00:41:46.420 --> 00:41:48.160 align:middle line:84%
I can go on more
vacations, and that's

00:41:48.160 --> 00:41:50.810 align:middle line:84%
what it means to
have a good life.

00:41:50.810 --> 00:41:53.560 align:middle line:84%
Well, if that's your
vision of a good life,

00:41:53.560 --> 00:41:56.109 align:middle line:84%
you can be compromised
pretty quickly.

00:41:56.109 --> 00:41:58.150 align:middle line:84%
People can say, well, you
can have the good life,

00:41:58.150 --> 00:42:00.056 align:middle line:90%
and I can give you this loan.

00:42:00.056 --> 00:42:01.930 align:middle line:84%
If you don't have the
money now, don't worry.

00:42:01.930 --> 00:42:04.535 align:middle line:90%
You'll get it.

00:42:04.535 --> 00:42:05.660 align:middle line:90%
Everybody else is doing it.

00:42:05.660 --> 00:42:07.430 align:middle line:90%
They're going to Disneyland.

00:42:07.430 --> 00:42:09.960 align:middle line:84%
You know, just put it
on your credit card.

00:42:09.960 --> 00:42:11.750 align:middle line:84%
Or you can get a
home equity loan out,

00:42:11.750 --> 00:42:14.520 align:middle line:84%
and you can have a
good, old, fun time.

00:42:14.520 --> 00:42:17.310 align:middle line:84%
So the heart of the
illusion and the issue

00:42:17.310 --> 00:42:21.370 align:middle line:84%
is the notion that you can
get something for nothing

00:42:21.370 --> 00:42:25.000 align:middle line:84%
and that taking and
consuming is the good life.

00:42:25.000 --> 00:42:25.960 align:middle line:90%
It's not.

00:42:25.960 --> 00:42:28.440 align:middle line:84%
America is an incredibly
creative country.

00:42:28.440 --> 00:42:29.560 align:middle line:90%
It's an inventive country.

00:42:29.560 --> 00:42:31.507 align:middle line:84%
Look at all the forms
of music, especially

00:42:31.507 --> 00:42:33.090 align:middle line:84%
within the
African-American community,

00:42:33.090 --> 00:42:35.350 align:middle line:90%
that have been created here.

00:42:35.350 --> 00:42:40.440 align:middle line:84%
Look at all the inventions
that have happened here.

00:42:40.440 --> 00:42:41.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Even in
the fantastical,

00:42:41.950 --> 00:42:44.020 align:middle line:84%
artistic realms,
just Hollywood alone.

00:42:44.020 --> 00:42:46.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ZEUS: Exactly, we're
talking the automobile.

00:42:46.400 --> 00:42:47.580 align:middle line:90%
We're talking electricity.

00:42:47.580 --> 00:42:48.850 align:middle line:90%
We're talking airplane.

00:42:48.850 --> 00:42:50.860 align:middle line:84%
We're talking-- it
just goes on and on.

00:42:50.860 --> 00:42:53.680 align:middle line:84%
So that's the real
American dream.

00:42:53.680 --> 00:42:56.470 align:middle line:84%
The real American dream
is to take our talent

00:42:56.470 --> 00:43:00.570 align:middle line:84%
to create and share and give
and find economic mechanisms

00:43:00.570 --> 00:43:02.320 align:middle line:84%
and ways of relating
to the community that

00:43:02.320 --> 00:43:04.040 align:middle line:90%
allow us to maximize that.

00:43:04.040 --> 00:43:08.450 align:middle line:84%
Not financial profit,
maximize creative intensity,

00:43:08.450 --> 00:43:11.360 align:middle line:84%
creative connection,
community connection.

00:43:11.360 --> 00:43:13.600 align:middle line:84%
And so what we need
to do is we need

00:43:13.600 --> 00:43:15.510 align:middle line:84%
to get off the
high-fructose corn

00:43:15.510 --> 00:43:19.840 align:middle line:84%
syrup of this
fantasy of consuming

00:43:19.840 --> 00:43:23.420 align:middle line:84%
your way into the good life,
which just leaves you morally

00:43:23.420 --> 00:43:26.670 align:middle line:84%
obese and morally
sick, and start

00:43:26.670 --> 00:43:31.750 align:middle line:84%
generating a notion of giving
and sharing and producing

00:43:31.750 --> 00:43:35.915 align:middle line:84%
and connecting as the
driver for the good life.

00:43:35.915 --> 00:43:37.740 align:middle line:84%
The nice thing about
a real good life

00:43:37.740 --> 00:43:39.620 align:middle line:90%
is it doesn't fit your image.

00:43:39.620 --> 00:43:41.830 align:middle line:84%
It comes out of your
growing and creating,

00:43:41.830 --> 00:43:44.850 align:middle line:90%
and it develops as you develop.

00:43:44.850 --> 00:43:47.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Number two is
get real about consequences

00:43:47.750 --> 00:43:50.580 align:middle line:84%
so that you can
anticipate the trends.

00:43:50.580 --> 00:43:53.790 align:middle line:84%
>>ZEUS: Right, so
let's say you happen

00:43:53.790 --> 00:43:58.960 align:middle line:84%
to be one of those people that
bought at the top of a market,

00:43:58.960 --> 00:44:03.070 align:middle line:84%
like your house now is worth
a lot less than it was.

00:44:03.070 --> 00:44:06.870 align:middle line:84%
And, oh, my stock, I mean, I
should have sold that stock

00:44:06.870 --> 00:44:07.780 align:middle line:90%
when it was--

00:44:07.780 --> 00:44:08.926 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, yeah.

00:44:08.926 --> 00:44:09.747 align:middle line:90%


00:44:09.747 --> 00:44:11.080 align:middle line:90%
>>ZEUS: And now it's worth half.

00:44:11.080 --> 00:44:13.420 align:middle line:84%
It's still a little bit
more than when I bought it,

00:44:13.420 --> 00:44:15.560 align:middle line:84%
but I'm waiting for it
to go back up again.

00:44:15.560 --> 00:44:18.610 align:middle line:84%
And again, that's part
of that same disease,

00:44:18.610 --> 00:44:23.350 align:middle line:84%
trying to maximize what you
can get out of something.

00:44:23.350 --> 00:44:25.770 align:middle line:84%
The fact is that
allowing yourself

00:44:25.770 --> 00:44:28.170 align:middle line:84%
to be sucked into
that mentality,

00:44:28.170 --> 00:44:32.960 align:middle line:84%
you're being sucked into a
scarcity model, where you're

00:44:32.960 --> 00:44:36.510 align:middle line:90%
being driven by what you lost.

00:44:36.510 --> 00:44:39.360 align:middle line:84%
And you want to get it
back by staying in the game

00:44:39.360 --> 00:44:41.190 align:middle line:90%
and continuing to play the game.

00:44:41.190 --> 00:44:44.490 align:middle line:84%
What I say in this paper is
you can actually gain more

00:44:44.490 --> 00:44:50.110 align:middle line:84%
in terms of quality of life by
admitting it didn't work out,

00:44:50.110 --> 00:44:51.250 align:middle line:90%
getting rid of it--

00:44:51.250 --> 00:44:54.109 align:middle line:90%


00:44:54.109 --> 00:44:56.400 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: So it's not plaguing
you on an emotional level.

00:44:56.400 --> 00:44:58.220 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: So it's not plaguing
you and weighing on you.

00:44:58.220 --> 00:44:59.720 align:middle line:84%
And there's something
really sort of

00:44:59.720 --> 00:45:02.300 align:middle line:84%
courageous and outrageous
about that action

00:45:02.300 --> 00:45:04.680 align:middle line:84%
that's very freeing,
very liberating.

00:45:04.680 --> 00:45:07.280 align:middle line:84%
Like, I won't be determined
by the objects around me.

00:45:07.280 --> 00:45:09.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to be determined
by the images of wealth

00:45:09.620 --> 00:45:11.230 align:middle line:90%
and the good life around me.

00:45:11.230 --> 00:45:14.860 align:middle line:84%
I could live on nothing, and
I don't have all that burden

00:45:14.860 --> 00:45:15.840 align:middle line:90%
on me.

00:45:15.840 --> 00:45:18.890 align:middle line:84%
And our family can learn to
work with other families.

00:45:18.890 --> 00:45:23.060 align:middle line:84%
We may even move in with another
family, co-housing, you know,

00:45:23.060 --> 00:45:26.360 align:middle line:84%
and share our resources,
reduce our housing

00:45:26.360 --> 00:45:29.270 align:middle line:90%
cost which is our highest cost.

00:45:29.270 --> 00:45:31.140 align:middle line:84%
Instead of thinking,
oh, well, maybe we

00:45:31.140 --> 00:45:33.740 align:middle line:84%
can scrape up enough to get
a slightly smaller house,

00:45:33.740 --> 00:45:36.495 align:middle line:90%
why not get more imaginative?

00:45:36.495 --> 00:45:37.370 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: You're right.

00:45:37.370 --> 00:45:38.324 align:middle line:90%
That's one thing.

00:45:38.324 --> 00:45:39.740 align:middle line:84%
The nice thing
about this country,

00:45:39.740 --> 00:45:41.440 align:middle line:84%
having so little
history, is that it

00:45:41.440 --> 00:45:46.640 align:middle line:84%
allows for the implementation
of whatever we can imagine.

00:45:46.640 --> 00:45:50.700 align:middle line:84%
We're not held back by a sense
of what's been done all along.

00:45:50.700 --> 00:45:54.260 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: And that's a
perfect way to look at it.

00:45:54.260 --> 00:45:56.720 align:middle line:84%
What will allow you to do
what you have imagined,

00:45:56.720 --> 00:45:58.030 align:middle line:90%
to be creative?

00:45:58.030 --> 00:46:01.490 align:middle line:84%
To be stuck in the old images
of what wealth and value is

00:46:01.490 --> 00:46:05.440 align:middle line:84%
that's hemmed you in
and has you working jobs

00:46:05.440 --> 00:46:08.530 align:middle line:84%
you don't like and has you
scraping by, or saying,

00:46:08.530 --> 00:46:10.060 align:middle line:90%
wait a minute.

00:46:10.060 --> 00:46:13.240 align:middle line:84%
The people who came into this
country came with nothing.

00:46:13.240 --> 00:46:15.760 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Right, that
is true, you know,

00:46:15.760 --> 00:46:18.900 align:middle line:84%
with the whole
downturn from 2008.

00:46:18.900 --> 00:46:22.400 align:middle line:84%
And I would certainly argue
we're in for another wild ride

00:46:22.400 --> 00:46:23.200 align:middle line:90%
here soon.

00:46:23.200 --> 00:46:24.436 align:middle line:90%
ZEUS: Oh, yes.

00:46:24.436 --> 00:46:27.020 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Yeah, and
we'll get to that,

00:46:27.020 --> 00:46:32.130 align:middle line:84%
is that it was giving people
an opportunity to rethink right

00:46:32.130 --> 00:46:36.090 align:middle line:84%
how they choose to live because
we all know that on one level

00:46:36.090 --> 00:46:38.680 align:middle line:84%
or another most of us
are slaves to a system.

00:46:38.680 --> 00:46:39.800 align:middle line:90%
We know that.

00:46:39.800 --> 00:46:42.670 align:middle line:84%
And we know that
you can't stand up

00:46:42.670 --> 00:46:44.610 align:middle line:84%
to your boss for fear
of losing your job.

00:46:44.610 --> 00:46:46.120 align:middle line:84%
And so you just
accept whatever's

00:46:46.120 --> 00:46:50.094 align:middle line:84%
going on in your life because
you have to pay those bills

00:46:50.094 --> 00:46:51.760 align:middle line:84%
or you have kids to
support and whatnot.

00:46:51.760 --> 00:46:56.150 align:middle line:84%
And so I think most people
understand that pain.

00:46:56.150 --> 00:46:59.360 align:middle line:84%
And so with the
economy shredding

00:46:59.360 --> 00:47:01.762 align:middle line:84%
as it did, more
or less, it really

00:47:01.762 --> 00:47:03.220 align:middle line:84%
gave people a chance
to rethink it.

00:47:03.220 --> 00:47:08.070 align:middle line:84%
But other than kids
struggling to find jobs,

00:47:08.070 --> 00:47:10.960 align:middle line:84%
young kids, people
who are in their 20s

00:47:10.960 --> 00:47:12.589 align:middle line:84%
not being able to
make it, moving back

00:47:12.589 --> 00:47:14.130 align:middle line:84%
in with their parents,
I haven't seen

00:47:14.130 --> 00:47:15.500 align:middle line:90%
a lot of creativity happening.

00:47:15.500 --> 00:47:18.512 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: No, no, because people
are still trying to eke it.

00:47:18.512 --> 00:47:20.470 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: They still think
it's going to recover.

00:47:20.470 --> 00:47:22.550 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: They still think
it's going to recover,

00:47:22.550 --> 00:47:26.110 align:middle line:84%
but jobs are contracting through
automation and et cetera.

00:47:26.110 --> 00:47:27.720 align:middle line:84%
And these jobs are
not coming back.

00:47:27.720 --> 00:47:29.490 align:middle line:84%
All throughout history,
we've gone to another thing.

00:47:29.490 --> 00:47:30.920 align:middle line:84%
We've gone agrarian
to industrial,

00:47:30.920 --> 00:47:34.910 align:middle line:84%
industrial to information age,
information age to, oh, wait

00:47:34.910 --> 00:47:36.080 align:middle line:90%
a minute.

00:47:36.080 --> 00:47:39.920 align:middle line:84%
We're getting rid of these jobs,
and they're not coming back.

00:47:39.920 --> 00:47:42.720 align:middle line:84%
So we have really got
to be creative about how

00:47:42.720 --> 00:47:43.810 align:middle line:90%
we exchange value.

00:47:43.810 --> 00:47:45.851 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Well, and that
gets us into number three.

00:47:45.851 --> 00:47:48.470 align:middle line:84%
Stop feeding the beast,
and act on your deeper

00:47:48.470 --> 00:47:50.470 align:middle line:90%
values and sense.

00:47:50.470 --> 00:47:52.950 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Yes, and I think
one of the examples that

00:47:52.950 --> 00:47:56.020 align:middle line:84%
resonates with a lot of people--
it might be in that section

00:47:56.020 --> 00:47:57.560 align:middle line:90%
there, where I'm like, listen.

00:47:57.560 --> 00:47:59.680 align:middle line:84%
How many of you have
a storage locker?

00:47:59.680 --> 00:48:02.450 align:middle line:84%
