you want to honor her memory.

00:48:11.330 --> 00:48:13.871 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: And you're paying $100
a month to keep all this junk.

00:48:13.871 --> 00:48:16.120 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Yes, and you
know that after a year,

00:48:16.120 --> 00:48:18.360 align:middle line:84%
you've already paid up for
the value of everything

00:48:18.360 --> 00:48:19.318 align:middle line:90%
in that storage locker.

00:48:19.318 --> 00:48:21.360 align:middle line:84%
And yet you're continuing
to keep it around.

00:48:21.360 --> 00:48:23.610 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Yes, and the example
you use up here I thought

00:48:23.610 --> 00:48:24.693 align:middle line:90%
was really cute.

00:48:24.693 --> 00:48:27.580 align:middle line:84%
It said, if you
cut yourself badly,

00:48:27.580 --> 00:48:29.750 align:middle line:84%
you don't worry about
all the blood you've lost

00:48:29.750 --> 00:48:32.026 align:middle line:90%
and how to get it back.

00:48:32.026 --> 00:48:36.840 align:middle line:84%
You stop the bleeding so you
won't lose any more blood.

00:48:36.840 --> 00:48:38.390 align:middle line:84%
And that's kind
of where you say,

00:48:38.390 --> 00:48:40.310 align:middle line:84%
we need to assess
ourselves right now.

00:48:40.310 --> 00:48:45.420 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Right, if something
is hemorrhaging you,

00:48:45.420 --> 00:48:48.730 align:middle line:84%
hemorrhaging your bank account,
even something as simple

00:48:48.730 --> 00:48:51.590 align:middle line:90%
as a storage locker, stop it.

00:48:51.590 --> 00:48:52.809 align:middle line:90%
Stop the bleeding.

00:48:52.809 --> 00:48:55.100 align:middle line:84%
How do you stop the bleeding
with a storage locker that

00:48:55.100 --> 00:48:57.270 align:middle line:84%
has junk in it
that you never use,

00:48:57.270 --> 00:48:59.850 align:middle line:84%
for reasons that aren't
really legitimate?

00:48:59.850 --> 00:49:01.510 align:middle line:84%
You're not honoring
your aunt's memory

00:49:01.510 --> 00:49:03.950 align:middle line:84%
by keeping something
in a dusty closet

00:49:03.950 --> 00:49:05.250 align:middle line:90%
that you're never going to use.

00:49:05.250 --> 00:49:08.630 align:middle line:84%
Give it to someone
who can use it.

00:49:08.630 --> 00:49:10.940 align:middle line:90%
That's honoring your memory.

00:49:10.940 --> 00:49:13.870 align:middle line:84%
And the same is true
of housing costs.

00:49:13.870 --> 00:49:18.060 align:middle line:84%
You know, if you're just
laboring under a mortgage,

00:49:18.060 --> 00:49:19.860 align:middle line:84%
and you can't really
pay it off, and you're

00:49:19.860 --> 00:49:22.471 align:middle line:84%
working two jobs to two and
a half jobs to pay it off,

00:49:22.471 --> 00:49:24.970 align:middle line:84%
and it's consuming the life you
could spend with your family

00:49:24.970 --> 00:49:28.050 align:middle line:84%
and friends and so forth,
then seriously consider

00:49:28.050 --> 00:49:30.510 align:middle line:84%
defaulting on it, well,
not defaulting, per se.

00:49:30.510 --> 00:49:32.930 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to be put in
a position of advocating

00:49:32.930 --> 00:49:37.110 align:middle line:84%
open default, but look
into your personal options,

00:49:37.110 --> 00:49:39.150 align:middle line:90%
into financial options.

00:49:39.150 --> 00:49:41.832 align:middle line:84%
And if it makes
sense, you know, you

00:49:41.832 --> 00:49:43.040 align:middle line:90%
can do other creative things.

00:49:43.040 --> 00:49:45.550 align:middle line:84%
You can have a family
move in with you perhaps,

00:49:45.550 --> 00:49:48.920 align:middle line:84%
or you can let go of
the house or downsize.

00:49:48.920 --> 00:49:51.000 align:middle line:84%
But the whole thing
is what you want to do

00:49:51.000 --> 00:49:53.009 align:middle line:84%
is move from an
unmanageable situation

00:49:53.009 --> 00:49:54.300 align:middle line:90%
to a more manageable situation.

00:49:54.300 --> 00:49:55.270 align:middle line:90%
You want to stop the bleeding.

00:49:55.270 --> 00:49:57.700 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Otherwise, life is
just a struggle and a burden.

00:49:57.700 --> 00:50:00.390 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Exactly, if you've
left that cut open,

00:50:00.390 --> 00:50:01.810 align:middle line:90%
you're going to become anemic.

00:50:01.810 --> 00:50:03.910 align:middle line:84%
It's going to affect
everything in your life.

00:50:03.910 --> 00:50:08.090 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it won't kill you, but
you're going to be anemic.

00:50:08.090 --> 00:50:09.840 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to
be able to enjoy life.

00:50:09.840 --> 00:50:12.210 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to be able
to make healthy connections.

00:50:12.210 --> 00:50:13.770 align:middle line:90%
You've got to stop it.

00:50:13.770 --> 00:50:16.670 align:middle line:84%
And we have always been taught
about how interesting accrues.

00:50:16.670 --> 00:50:18.490 align:middle line:84%
You've got to save
early, and then it's

00:50:18.490 --> 00:50:20.290 align:middle line:90%
going to be exponential.

00:50:20.290 --> 00:50:23.440 align:middle line:84%
But hardly anyone talks
about cutting your costs.

00:50:23.440 --> 00:50:25.850 align:middle line:90%
It has the same effect.

00:50:25.850 --> 00:50:29.510 align:middle line:84%
If you cut a cost or
stop the bleeding early,

00:50:29.510 --> 00:50:31.760 align:middle line:84%
it's going to have exponential
effects for your future

00:50:31.760 --> 00:50:34.680 align:middle line:84%
as well by eliminating
the negatives

00:50:34.680 --> 00:50:38.480 align:middle line:84%
and drains on your resources
in very much the same way.

00:50:38.480 --> 00:50:40.760 align:middle line:84%
So that's one thing
you don't hear much,

00:50:40.760 --> 00:50:42.280 align:middle line:90%
and it's absolutely crucial.

00:50:42.280 --> 00:50:43.930 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Yes, I agree with that.

00:50:43.930 --> 00:50:48.010 align:middle line:84%
I do know of one situation
where a woman's parents had

00:50:48.010 --> 00:50:50.960 align:middle line:84%
reached retirement age, and
she was living by herself.

00:50:50.960 --> 00:50:53.090 align:middle line:84%
And they each had
mortgages, and so they

00:50:53.090 --> 00:50:55.890 align:middle line:84%
decided to sell their
individual homes

00:50:55.890 --> 00:50:57.880 align:middle line:84%
and then buy a home
that had two master

00:50:57.880 --> 00:51:00.300 align:middle line:84%
suites-- it was a
good enough size--

00:51:00.300 --> 00:51:01.945 align:middle line:90%
and then just collaborate.

00:51:01.945 --> 00:51:04.650 align:middle line:90%


00:51:04.650 --> 00:51:05.720 align:middle line:90%
They're from India.

00:51:05.720 --> 00:51:07.770 align:middle line:84%
The mother did the
cooking for everybody,

00:51:07.770 --> 00:51:10.917 align:middle line:84%
so my friend had fabulous
food around all the time.

00:51:10.917 --> 00:51:12.500 align:middle line:84%
She had someone to
watch her dogs when

00:51:12.500 --> 00:51:15.520 align:middle line:84%
she wanted to go on
vacation and actually

00:51:15.520 --> 00:51:19.830 align:middle line:84%
had a much higher quality of
life as a result of their just

00:51:19.830 --> 00:51:22.400 align:middle line:84%
deciding to get creative
and do this together.

00:51:22.400 --> 00:51:24.740 align:middle line:84%
But then again, their
culture is more collaborative

00:51:24.740 --> 00:51:26.460 align:middle line:90%
and family oriented.

00:51:26.460 --> 00:51:28.350 align:middle line:84%
We tend not to see
that as an option

00:51:28.350 --> 00:51:31.750 align:middle line:84%
because it's somehow a weakness
or a failure if you're older

00:51:31.750 --> 00:51:33.670 align:middle line:84%
and you just haven't
saved enough to make

00:51:33.670 --> 00:51:35.810 align:middle line:90%
it work in your elderly years.

00:51:35.810 --> 00:51:37.930 align:middle line:84%
Or if you're young and
you haven't made it work,

00:51:37.930 --> 00:51:41.750 align:middle line:84%
either way, we're failures if
we can't have our own domain.

00:51:41.750 --> 00:51:45.590 align:middle line:84%
That's so false, and it's
just so disconnective.

00:51:45.590 --> 00:51:49.740 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Yes, yes, that's a
different kind of accounting.

00:51:49.740 --> 00:51:52.630 align:middle line:90%
That's a life accounting.

00:51:52.630 --> 00:51:55.050 align:middle line:84%
And being real with the
numbers of life accounting,

00:51:55.050 --> 00:51:57.360 align:middle line:90%
it's creating value.

00:51:57.360 --> 00:52:00.210 align:middle line:84%
It's creating quality
of life because now you

00:52:00.210 --> 00:52:02.210 align:middle line:84%
don't have to hire and
do everything yourself.

00:52:02.210 --> 00:52:03.180 align:middle line:90%
You actually have help.

00:52:03.180 --> 00:52:05.096 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: It worked way
better for both of them.

00:52:05.096 --> 00:52:06.230 align:middle line:90%
ZEUS: Of course, it does.

00:52:06.230 --> 00:52:08.130 align:middle line:84%
And the millennials
are getting this.

00:52:08.130 --> 00:52:10.990 align:middle line:84%
They're forced into it, but
they're starting to do this.

00:52:10.990 --> 00:52:13.448 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: As long as they're not
smoking weed in the basement

00:52:13.448 --> 00:52:16.840 align:middle line:84%
and playing video games, which
a lot of them kids do do.

00:52:16.840 --> 00:52:19.460 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you've got to stand up
and still offer what you have,

00:52:19.460 --> 00:52:22.050 align:middle line:84%
whatever your skills,
talents, gifts, passions are.

00:52:22.050 --> 00:52:24.760 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Right, and I have talked
to you about this earlier.

00:52:24.760 --> 00:52:27.540 align:middle line:84%
I'm passionate about big
helping millennials get together

00:52:27.540 --> 00:52:30.750 align:middle line:84%
to realize that they can work
better together than simply

00:52:30.750 --> 00:52:33.510 align:middle line:84%
going back to their
parents' basement

00:52:33.510 --> 00:52:36.630 align:middle line:84%
and addressing in a social
entrepreneurial way community

00:52:36.630 --> 00:52:39.200 align:middle line:84%
needs and working with
schools to get them

00:52:39.200 --> 00:52:43.220 align:middle line:84%
outside of the building and get
them to do applied knowledge.

00:52:43.220 --> 00:52:46.210 align:middle line:84%
You know, so that education
comes back around again.

00:52:46.210 --> 00:52:47.010 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: It does.

00:52:47.010 --> 00:52:49.343 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the thing is we're
working our way through this,

00:52:49.343 --> 00:52:52.540 align:middle line:84%
but you have an equal
amount of lucidity

00:52:52.540 --> 00:52:54.150 align:middle line:90%
on the subject of education.

00:52:54.150 --> 00:52:56.390 align:middle line:84%
And at the very
end, we'll talk just

00:52:56.390 --> 00:52:58.757 align:middle line:84%
for a minute about another
passion that you have

00:52:58.757 --> 00:53:00.590 align:middle line:84%
and what you're trying
to contribute to kids

00:53:00.590 --> 00:53:04.060 align:middle line:90%
who appear to be challenged.

00:53:04.060 --> 00:53:06.170 align:middle line:84%
OK, so finally we
have step number four,

00:53:06.170 --> 00:53:08.530 align:middle line:84%
confront your habits
and then start

00:53:08.530 --> 00:53:10.429 align:middle line:84%
transforming your
actual character.

00:53:10.429 --> 00:53:12.470 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Now this is one of
the most difficult steps

00:53:12.470 --> 00:53:15.910 align:middle line:84%
for an American because
Americans' identity,

00:53:15.910 --> 00:53:18.900 align:middle line:84%
they build their
identity like a suit.

00:53:18.900 --> 00:53:21.430 align:middle line:84%
And we all kind of
agree to that identity.

00:53:21.430 --> 00:53:23.250 align:middle line:84%
You go to LA, and
you can see that.

00:53:23.250 --> 00:53:25.340 align:middle line:84%
Everyone wants to be a
star, and everyone kind of

00:53:25.340 --> 00:53:29.250 align:middle line:90%
has to agree to that game.

00:53:29.250 --> 00:53:30.950 align:middle line:84%
So you spend more
money than you have.

00:53:30.950 --> 00:53:32.800 align:middle line:84%
You have this nice
car and so forth.

00:53:32.800 --> 00:53:37.290 align:middle line:84%
And yet at the same
time, in LA people

00:53:37.290 --> 00:53:39.010 align:middle line:84%
have stopped as I'm
crossing a street

00:53:39.010 --> 00:53:40.968 align:middle line:84%
or stopped to allow me
to go across the street.

00:53:40.968 --> 00:53:46.540 align:middle line:84%
You know, so it's this odd
mix that I like of aspiration

00:53:46.540 --> 00:53:48.470 align:middle line:90%
mixed with materialism.

00:53:48.470 --> 00:53:50.700 align:middle line:84%
I'm not so keen on
that, but I realize

00:53:50.700 --> 00:53:53.000 align:middle line:84%
it's part of the
American character,

00:53:53.000 --> 00:53:55.580 align:middle line:84%
and then mixed with
this desire to succeed.

00:53:55.580 --> 00:53:59.590 align:middle line:84%
And it's very difficult
for an American

00:53:59.590 --> 00:54:01.510 align:middle line:84%
to step back and say
that they're wrong

00:54:01.510 --> 00:54:03.430 align:middle line:84%
or this is not
working because it's

00:54:03.430 --> 00:54:05.350 align:middle line:84%
like if I let go
of this identity

00:54:05.350 --> 00:54:08.960 align:middle line:84%
that I've spent all this
time building up, who am I?

00:54:08.960 --> 00:54:13.270 align:middle line:84%
And I want to say, you're the
person creatively adapting.

00:54:13.270 --> 00:54:14.840 align:middle line:90%
You're not your mask.

00:54:14.840 --> 00:54:16.595 align:middle line:90%
You're not your identity.

00:54:16.595 --> 00:54:19.620 align:middle line:84%
You're the one inside
that can throw this off

00:54:19.620 --> 00:54:24.730 align:middle line:84%
completely and say, I'm
a creative American.

00:54:24.730 --> 00:54:27.320 align:middle line:84%
I can let all of this go and
create a completely different

00:54:27.320 --> 00:54:28.270 align:middle line:90%
life if I want to.

00:54:28.270 --> 00:54:30.410 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Absolutely, and
it allows for passion

00:54:30.410 --> 00:54:33.630 align:middle line:84%
to flow back in in your
endeavors, which we've lost.

00:54:33.630 --> 00:54:36.730 align:middle line:84%
There's no energy left
for any kind of passion,

00:54:36.730 --> 00:54:39.260 align:middle line:84%
really, in the
American lifestyle.

00:54:39.260 --> 00:54:42.310 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Unfortunately, there
isn't, not in this mode.

00:54:42.310 --> 00:54:45.710 align:middle line:84%
There are glimmers of
it, but people are timid.

00:54:45.710 --> 00:54:47.750 align:middle line:84%
I think that people are
being invited-- this

00:54:47.750 --> 00:54:49.430 align:middle line:90%
is the good thing about this.

00:54:49.430 --> 00:54:51.790 align:middle line:84%
We're being invited with the
collapse of a system that

00:54:51.790 --> 00:54:53.620 align:middle line:84%
has been very inauthentic
and has served us

00:54:53.620 --> 00:54:57.260 align:middle line:84%
poorly to step forward in
a positive, healthy way.

00:54:57.260 --> 00:55:00.890 align:middle line:84%
The problem again is that
we have to not only confront

00:55:00.890 --> 00:55:04.330 align:middle line:84%
the outside aspects of
it, like spending money

00:55:04.330 --> 00:55:05.571 align:middle line:90%
that we don't need.

00:55:05.571 --> 00:55:07.820 align:middle line:84%
But we have to confront the
inner aspects of it, which

00:55:07.820 --> 00:55:10.570 align:middle line:84%
is this step number
four, your character.

00:55:10.570 --> 00:55:12.470 align:middle line:84%
It says, what are
my little addictions

00:55:12.470 --> 00:55:15.080 align:middle line:84%
and my worries that keep
me going into the game

00:55:15.080 --> 00:55:17.840 align:middle line:84%
that I know deep in my
heart is completely over?

00:55:17.840 --> 00:55:18.640 align:middle line:90%
It's done.

00:55:18.640 --> 00:55:19.220 align:middle line:90%
It's bankrupt.

00:55:19.220 --> 00:55:19.930 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: It's killing
me, right, yeah.

00:55:19.930 --> 00:55:20.980 align:middle line:90%
ZEUS: It's killing me.

00:55:20.980 --> 00:55:23.830 align:middle line:84%
And to have not only
the courage individually

00:55:23.830 --> 00:55:28.150 align:middle line:84%
but together to get outside of
that classic American isolated

00:55:28.150 --> 00:55:31.409 align:middle line:84%
individualism and to start
to speak up and have courage

00:55:31.409 --> 00:55:33.700 align:middle line:84%
because when you do that,
then the other people go, oh.

00:55:33.700 --> 00:55:35.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm not the only one
thinking this way.

00:55:35.990 --> 00:55:37.640 align:middle line:84%
And before you know
it, you can start

00:55:37.640 --> 00:55:40.510 align:middle line:84%
creating discussion
groups, groups

00:55:40.510 --> 00:55:43.620 align:middle line:84%
where you decide maybe you're
going to go in together

00:55:43.620 --> 00:55:47.090 align:middle line:84%
to buy larger lots of food
and spend less money on that

00:55:47.090 --> 00:55:50.250 align:middle line:84%
and maybe even start a
co-op as a result of that.

00:55:50.250 --> 00:55:51.860 align:middle line:84%
So these are the
kinds of things that

00:55:51.860 --> 00:55:55.050 align:middle line:84%
will allow the American
creativity to come together.

00:55:55.050 --> 00:55:58.080 align:middle line:84%
This community, getting outside
of the isolated individualism

00:55:58.080 --> 00:56:01.350 align:middle line:84%
is to not identify yourself
with your mask of your identity,

00:56:01.350 --> 00:56:02.550 align:middle line:90%
with your dream.

00:56:02.550 --> 00:56:04.450 align:middle line:84%
Your dream is something
that's continual.

00:56:04.450 --> 00:56:05.860 align:middle line:90%
It's creative.

00:56:05.860 --> 00:56:07.050 align:middle line:90%
It's not a caricature.

00:56:07.050 --> 00:56:08.690 align:middle line:90%
It's not a cartoon.

00:56:08.690 --> 00:56:10.540 align:middle line:90%
It's not an image.

00:56:10.540 --> 00:56:12.330 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we
have to get away from.

00:56:12.330 --> 00:56:14.621 align:middle line:84%
Because we're are so wrapped
up with reality television

00:56:14.621 --> 00:56:19.002 align:middle line:84%
and stuff about image, we
need to break that habit.

00:56:19.002 --> 00:56:20.085 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: I agree with that.

00:56:20.085 --> 00:56:22.930 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting because
what you're talking about,

00:56:22.930 --> 00:56:25.130 align:middle line:84%
all of this again,
if you weren't

00:56:25.130 --> 00:56:28.820 align:middle line:84%
looking at it in these bit-sized
pieces, seems overwhelming.

00:56:28.820 --> 00:56:30.790 align:middle line:84%
But when you put this
together, you see,

00:56:30.790 --> 00:56:34.350 align:middle line:84%
gee, the problem actually you
