00:56:34.350 --> 00:56:36.860 align:middle line:84%
And it's sick, but
it's relatively easy

00:56:36.860 --> 00:56:38.670 align:middle line:84%
to understand the way
you break it down.

00:56:38.670 --> 00:56:40.690 align:middle line:84%
And the solutions
are too, but it

00:56:40.690 --> 00:56:44.510 align:middle line:84%
does require an accounting
of one's own life.

00:56:44.510 --> 00:56:46.610 align:middle line:84%
And the way you've
put this together, you

00:56:46.610 --> 00:56:48.760 align:middle line:84%
say you're going to make
these documents available?

00:56:48.760 --> 00:56:49.150 align:middle line:90%
ZEUS: Yeah, sure.

00:56:49.150 --> 00:56:51.070 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: That's great
because it really

00:56:51.070 --> 00:56:53.790 align:middle line:84%
does give a focal point for
people to gather together,

00:56:53.790 --> 00:56:56.860 align:middle line:84%
whether it's a family
or, again, a community,

00:56:56.860 --> 00:56:59.020 align:middle line:84%
or a group of young
people who really

00:56:59.020 --> 00:57:00.769 align:middle line:84%
are trying to figure
out, how are we going

00:57:00.769 --> 00:57:02.560 align:middle line:90%
to make the rent, you know?

00:57:02.560 --> 00:57:06.450 align:middle line:84%
The last one is liberate
yourself and get proactive.

00:57:06.450 --> 00:57:08.340 align:middle line:90%
ZEUS: Right, and that's it.

00:57:08.340 --> 00:57:13.300 align:middle line:84%
Again, this is a
joyful endeavor.

00:57:13.300 --> 00:57:16.720 align:middle line:84%
I think that a large part
of what's keeping people

00:57:16.720 --> 00:57:21.120 align:middle line:84%
from taking this not so
radical but actually quite

00:57:21.120 --> 00:57:24.850 align:middle line:84%
joyous step of stopping
what's not working, inside

00:57:24.850 --> 00:57:28.080 align:middle line:84%
and outside, and moving
into the creative realm

00:57:28.080 --> 00:57:29.510 align:middle line:84%
is this notion
that, one, they're

00:57:29.510 --> 00:57:30.890 align:middle line:90%
going to lose something.

00:57:30.890 --> 00:57:35.040 align:middle line:84%
Or, two, it's going
to be too risky.

00:57:35.040 --> 00:57:37.510 align:middle line:84%
Like, it's going to be
riskier than having nothing?

00:57:37.510 --> 00:57:39.510 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Riskier than what
they're already doing?

00:57:39.510 --> 00:57:42.070 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: And being
miserable having nothing?

00:57:42.070 --> 00:57:43.370 align:middle line:90%
I've told young people.

00:57:43.370 --> 00:57:45.430 align:middle line:84%
I've said, there's
never been a better time

00:57:45.430 --> 00:57:48.060 align:middle line:84%
to be who you are
because even selling out

00:57:48.060 --> 00:57:50.682 align:middle line:90%
is not paying anymore.

00:57:50.682 --> 00:57:52.390 align:middle line:84%
You could sell out to
become that lawyer.

00:57:52.390 --> 00:57:55.370 align:middle line:84%
Now you have $400,000 of debt,
and you don't have a job.

00:57:55.370 --> 00:57:59.000 align:middle line:84%
You did the responsible thing,
and it's not working either.

00:57:59.000 --> 00:58:01.300 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: I love it,
even when selling out

00:58:01.300 --> 00:58:03.010 align:middle line:90%
doesn't make a profit.

00:58:03.010 --> 00:58:06.300 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Yes, so I wanted to say,
you're not losing anything.

00:58:06.300 --> 00:58:08.850 align:middle line:84%
You're facing the realities of
the world in which the selling

00:58:08.850 --> 00:58:12.660 align:middle line:84%
out actually ends up making
you worse off than actually

00:58:12.660 --> 00:58:14.690 align:middle line:90%
following your own passion.

00:58:14.690 --> 00:58:16.320 align:middle line:90%
You're in less debt.

00:58:16.320 --> 00:58:19.280 align:middle line:84%
You're doing something
at least you care about,

00:58:19.280 --> 00:58:21.550 align:middle line:84%
and you're not being
abused and mistreated

00:58:21.550 --> 00:58:23.510 align:middle line:84%
by organizations or
corporations that

00:58:23.510 --> 00:58:27.800 align:middle line:84%
want to take every last
dime out of your hide

00:58:27.800 --> 00:58:31.280 align:middle line:84%
and every last sweat out
of you to make profit

00:58:31.280 --> 00:58:33.160 align:middle line:90%
and to ship it off to the 1%.

00:58:33.160 --> 00:58:37.640 align:middle line:84%
So before there was
at least a bargain

00:58:37.640 --> 00:58:39.100 align:middle line:90%
to be made with the devil.

00:58:39.100 --> 00:58:40.540 align:middle line:84%
There isn't that
bargain anymore.

00:58:40.540 --> 00:58:41.850 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: We already did that.

00:58:41.850 --> 00:58:43.558 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: We've already
done that, and that's

00:58:43.558 --> 00:58:47.010 align:middle line:84%
what got us in this
place in the first place.

00:58:47.010 --> 00:58:51.700 align:middle line:84%
So I really want to emphasize
that this is a step of joy.

00:58:51.700 --> 00:58:53.280 align:middle line:90%
It's not admitting failure.

00:58:53.280 --> 00:58:57.800 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like a
humorous acknowledgement.

00:58:57.800 --> 00:58:58.950 align:middle line:90%
It's all gone downhill.

00:58:58.950 --> 00:59:00.864 align:middle line:84%
Even selling out
has gone downhill.

00:59:00.864 --> 00:59:03.430 align:middle line:84%
And to have that kind
of good American humor

00:59:03.430 --> 00:59:05.972 align:middle line:84%
and good global
humor to say, OK,

00:59:05.972 --> 00:59:07.930 align:middle line:84%
especially if you're in
the younger generation,

00:59:07.930 --> 00:59:08.400 align:middle line:90%
let's get inventive.

00:59:08.400 --> 00:59:09.480 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: It's all an experiment.

00:59:09.480 --> 00:59:10.563 align:middle line:90%
This is how that one went.

00:59:10.563 --> 00:59:12.390 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: It's an
experiment, and then

00:59:12.390 --> 00:59:14.950 align:middle line:84%
start using some of the
material in the book.

00:59:14.950 --> 00:59:17.280 align:middle line:84%
Start developing some
of your own experiments

00:59:17.280 --> 00:59:20.620 align:middle line:84%
to see what can actually
increase your quality of life

00:59:20.620 --> 00:59:23.570 align:middle line:90%
and actually decrease the cost.

00:59:23.570 --> 00:59:26.080 align:middle line:90%
And pool your resources.

00:59:26.080 --> 00:59:28.260 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: And draw back your
energy for, as you say,

00:59:28.260 --> 00:59:30.450 align:middle line:84%
where you really
choose to use it for.

00:59:30.450 --> 00:59:32.610 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Right, and
it will accelerate

00:59:32.610 --> 00:59:34.800 align:middle line:84%
the downfall of the
sickness because once

00:59:34.800 --> 00:59:37.110 align:middle line:84%
you withdraw your energy
away from the sickness,

00:59:37.110 --> 00:59:38.794 align:middle line:84%
then it doesn't have
anything to go on.

00:59:38.794 --> 00:59:39.960 align:middle line:90%
It starts to consume itself.

00:59:39.960 --> 00:59:41.168 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Yeah, it has no food.

00:59:41.168 --> 00:59:42.240 align:middle line:90%
ZEUS: It has no food.

00:59:42.240 --> 00:59:44.280 align:middle line:84%
So it's almost a
moral obligation

00:59:44.280 --> 00:59:46.440 align:middle line:84%
to do that as well as
a personal opportunity

00:59:46.440 --> 00:59:48.060 align:middle line:90%
and a communal opportunity.

00:59:48.060 --> 00:59:51.240 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: And so with what's
coming up economically, I mean,

00:59:51.240 --> 00:59:54.740 align:middle line:84%
we hear various forecasts at
the beginning of the year.

00:59:54.740 --> 00:59:56.411 align:middle line:90%
And I pay attention.

00:59:56.411 --> 00:59:58.660 align:middle line:84%
You pay attention to probably
some of the same people.

00:59:58.660 --> 01:00:02.370 align:middle line:90%


01:00:02.370 --> 01:00:04.730 align:middle line:84%
Let's use 2007-2008
as an example.

01:00:04.730 --> 01:00:07.530 align:middle line:84%
What's it look
like for 2016-2017?

01:00:07.530 --> 01:00:08.390 align:middle line:90%
What's coming up?

01:00:08.390 --> 01:00:14.224 align:middle line:84%
ZEUS: Well, my book has
been very, very accurate.

01:00:14.224 --> 01:00:15.640 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to do
an update on this,

01:00:15.640 --> 01:00:18.710 align:middle line:84%
but there's really
not much to update.

01:00:18.710 --> 01:00:21.970 align:middle line:84%
In this, I made these comments
like, the fundamentals will not

01:00:21.970 --> 01:00:23.310 align:middle line:90%
be followed.

01:00:23.310 --> 01:00:25.890 align:middle line:84%
The interests of
the hyper-wealthy

01:00:25.890 --> 01:00:28.410 align:middle line:84%
will continue to predominate
over the general interest,

01:00:28.410 --> 01:00:29.993 align:middle line:84%
and these things
have begun to happen.

01:00:29.993 --> 01:00:31.876 align:middle line:90%


01:00:31.876 --> 01:00:33.500 align:middle line:84%
And what's happened
is the bigger banks

01:00:33.500 --> 01:00:35.070 align:middle line:90%
have gotten even bigger.

01:00:35.070 --> 01:00:39.610 align:middle line:84%
So the problems that
gave rise to 2008

01:00:39.610 --> 01:00:44.460 align:middle line:84%
have increased behind the
scenes, and people can feel it.

01:00:44.460 --> 01:00:46.650 align:middle line:84%
They are struggling
more and more.

01:00:46.650 --> 01:00:49.170 align:middle line:84%
They have hollowed out
their retirement accounts,

01:00:49.170 --> 01:00:52.310 align:middle line:84%
gotten into greater debt to
finance even a minimal life,

01:00:52.310 --> 01:00:55.195 align:middle line:84%
even a contracted or
lowered lifestyle.

01:00:55.195 --> 01:00:58.760 align:middle line:90%
And it's still not adequate.

01:00:58.760 --> 01:01:00.510 align:middle line:84%
And jobs are now
shrinking because they're

01:01:00.510 --> 01:01:02.190 align:middle line:84%
being automated and
so forth, and the jobs

01:01:02.190 --> 01:01:03.660 align:middle line:84%
that are being put
into the economy

01:01:03.660 --> 01:01:06.740 align:middle line:90%
are half the salary or less.

01:01:06.740 --> 01:01:10.040 align:middle line:84%
They're lower-level service jobs
or part time with no benefits

01:01:10.040 --> 01:01:11.390 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

01:01:11.390 --> 01:01:14.880 align:middle line:84%
So this, again,
is going to build.

01:01:14.880 --> 01:01:19.190 align:middle line:84%
Before, I thought-- that's why
I tried to get this book out.

01:01:19.190 --> 01:01:24.540 align:middle line:84%
I was thinking,
2014, maybe 2016.

01:01:24.540 --> 01:01:26.460 align:middle line:84%
What I found is that
the technologies

01:01:26.460 --> 01:01:29.390 align:middle line:84%
for pushing off the
consciousness and reckoning

01:01:29.390 --> 01:01:30.250 align:middle line:90%
are well developed.

01:01:30.250 --> 01:01:32.380 align:middle line:84%
The American people
have allowed themselves

01:01:32.380 --> 01:01:35.017 align:middle line:84%
to be pulled into it
because they don't

01:01:35.017 --> 01:01:36.100 align:middle line:90%
want the reckoning either.

01:01:36.100 --> 01:01:40.330 align:middle line:84%
A part of them doesn't,
but it can't last forever.

01:01:40.330 --> 01:01:43.420 align:middle line:84%
When it comes, it's going
to be worse than 2008.

01:01:43.420 --> 01:01:45.080 align:middle line:84%
I do think it's
probably going to come

01:01:45.080 --> 01:01:49.170 align:middle line:84%
within this presidential
term, from 2016 to 2020.

01:01:49.170 --> 01:01:51.970 align:middle line:84%
Honestly, looking
at the trends, I

01:01:51.970 --> 01:01:55.430 align:middle line:90%
don't see it going beyond 2020.

01:01:55.430 --> 01:01:57.125 align:middle line:90%
There's just too much happening.

01:01:57.125 --> 01:01:59.000 align:middle line:84%
Baby boomers retiring,
they're going to drop,

01:01:59.000 --> 01:02:01.010 align:middle line:84%
need much more medical
care, and so forth.

01:02:01.010 --> 01:02:03.160 align:middle line:84%
So there are going to be
stresses on the system.

01:02:03.160 --> 01:02:05.330 align:middle line:84%
Young people, they're
sitting around,

01:02:05.330 --> 01:02:08.490 align:middle line:84%
waiting for jobs that
are not materializing.

01:02:08.490 --> 01:02:11.920 align:middle line:84%
And also they themselves are
pushing for accountability.

01:02:11.920 --> 01:02:14.480 align:middle line:84%
You saw this in the tremendous
support of Bernie Sanders.

01:02:14.480 --> 01:02:20.009 align:middle line:84%
They're looking for a way to--
they're saying, wait a minute.

01:02:20.009 --> 01:02:21.800 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to
accept this rigged game.

01:02:21.800 --> 01:02:24.560 align:middle line:84%
We're going to get involved--
politically, culturally,

01:02:24.560 --> 01:02:27.060 align:middle line:84%
and socially in
our communities--

01:02:27.060 --> 01:02:29.280 align:middle line:84%
with meeting these needs
that are not being met.

01:02:29.280 --> 01:02:33.140 align:middle line:84%
So that's both positive
and creating a resistance

01:02:33.140 --> 01:02:35.740 align:middle line:84%
to business as usual that
these things come around.

01:02:35.740 --> 01:02:38.320 align:middle line:84%
Now I'm not advocating
any particular candidate.

01:02:38.320 --> 01:02:44.400 align:middle line:84%
So I don't want to be
juxtaposing candidates.

01:02:44.400 --> 01:02:48.240 align:middle line:84%
But what I am
advocating for is a way

01:02:48.240 --> 01:02:52.840 align:middle line:84%
of going forward into the
future in which we are clear

01:02:52.840 --> 01:02:56.750 align:middle line:84%
of what the possible
creative possibilities are

01:02:56.750 --> 01:02:59.170 align:middle line:84%
and where the real
damage is happening.

01:02:59.170 --> 01:03:02.290 align:middle line:84%
And again, coming
up to the housing

01:03:02.290 --> 01:03:07.070 align:middle line:84%
market when people are saying,
who could have known, I did.

01:03:07.070 --> 01:03:08.365 align:middle line:90%
I wrote about it.

01:03:08.365 --> 01:03:09.250 align:middle line:90%
And look at it.

01:03:09.250 --> 01:03:14.760 align:middle line:84%
You have houses in the Bay Area
that are three times the rent.

01:03:14.760 --> 01:03:17.390 align:middle line:84%
For the same house, you
are paying a mortgage

01:03:17.390 --> 01:03:19.540 align:middle line:84%
that is three times
what you would pay

01:03:19.540 --> 01:03:21.885 align:middle line:90%
for that same house in rent.

01:03:21.885 --> 01:03:25.020 align:middle line:90%
That cannot continue.

01:03:25.020 --> 01:03:27.520 align:middle line:90%
It is so skewed.

01:03:27.520 --> 01:03:31.210 align:middle line:84%
And the only thing that would
not allow a person to say this

01:03:31.210 --> 01:03:34.580 align:middle line:84%
is going to collapse
sooner rather

01:03:34.580 --> 01:03:37.376 align:middle line:84%
than later is to just
delude yourself and say, oh.

01:03:37.376 --> 01:03:38.750 align:middle line:84%
The market's just
going to go up.

01:03:38.750 --> 01:03:40.520 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: One little
glimmer of hope

01:03:40.520 --> 01:03:44.480 align:middle line:84%
which we see on television,
some of the good side of media,

01:03:44.480 --> 01:03:46.930 align:middle line:84%
is the notion of these
little mini homes

01:03:46.930 --> 01:03:50.240 align:middle line:84%
